  abstract = "Turmoil has engulfed psychological science. Causes and
              consequences of the reproducibility crisis are in dispute. With
              the hope of addressing some of its aspects, Bayesian methods are
              gaining increasing attention in psychological science. Some of
              their advantages, as opposed to the frequentist framework, are
              the ability to describe parameters in probabilistic terms and
              explicitly incorporate prior knowledge about them into the model.
